<br>
So, I finally got to put some play time in on Sullon.  First impression?  I don't think I'll be leaving this server any time soon.  It's a blast.<br>
<br>
I started a Human Enchanter following Rodcet.  That started me in Qeynos and on the Good team.  I knew Good was going to have it rough in terms of numbers, but I really wanted to play on the underdog team.  I also wanted to be able to hunt in Black Burrow again and romp around my old playground of Qeynos Hills.<br>
<br>
While I got to start in Qeynos and be on the Good team, like I wanted, I soon learned that it's going to be a little while before I get to hunt in Black Burrow and zip around Qeynos Hills avoiding Tovax and dodging Rabid Grizzies.<br>
<br>
I level up to 5 pretty quickly.  I must say, I love that feeling you get when you scrape together the Gold and Silver to buy your spells.  One by one I managed to pick up my first and forth level spells.  I still (at level eight) don't have them all but every time I buy one, I'm totally satisfied.  It's like playing back during the release with 50 times more content, a stable connection and a few less bugs.<br>
<br>
@#%$, I would be wandering around North Qeynos and hear the /shouts from people saying the Queen was out.  Took me a few seconds to realize that it was the bug Queen in the newbie area.  I remember that bitch.  She killed me like 80 times when I was a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Newbie</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> newbie (as opposed to a PvP newbie).  Ahh, the memories.<br>
<br>
Well, I wandered out into Qeynos Hills.  Only a few bubbles from level 6 and that line that everybody else but me seemed to be confident to cross.<br>
<br>
Let me digress now to mention that the Good team is TOTALLY outnumbered.  Whereas before when I conned people and saw the &quot;threateningly&quot; report, I didn't pay attention... I now saw enemies eyeing me suspiciously.  They're everywhere.  On occasion, I'd see &quot;ally&quot;.  But it was rare and usually a blur (as they ran past me, fearful to stop).<br>
<br>
I felt like a human on the Planet of the Apes.<br>
<br>
Well, after a few more kills I managed to ding into PvP territory.  I immediately did what I've now patented as, the super spin.  It's where you whirl around to do a quick &quot;check six&quot; to make sure you have no bogies on your tail (sorry folks, I'm a <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.hitechcreations.com">fighter pilot</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> at heart).  I didn't notice anyone, so I did a few quick kills to get a small buffer and ran into town to sell some stuff.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://gaming.wlvrn.com/ss/ohboy.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
I head out to kill some more bats in Qeynos Hills.  I end up dawdling around though... looking for beetles to kill for the eyes.  Over a Silver per eye is a killing for me.  Over the next half hour, my guard goes down as I get more relaxed.<br>
<br>
On my way back to zone into Qeynos, I notice a bunch of people sitting near the zone line.  I approach and take a look.  I guess it was just curiosity.  They conned white and apprehensive and I wanted to see what they were up to.<br>
<br>
Well, as I'm standing there, I'm rooted.  Then this Mage and Warrior (Rogue, Warrior... some kind of melee) start ripping me up.  I manage to get off a Color Flux which stuns them all for a bit.  As I try to mez the melee, he breaks free just in time to interrupt my attempt.  Many fizzles and interrupts later, I'm dead.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   &quot; DAMN YOU!  Damn you all to hell! &quot;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> -Heston<br>
<br>
My first time being wacked PvP.  My heart is pumping.  I end up back in the Qeynos newbie area, re-mem my spells and head back out... WAAAAY to the right as to avoid zoning into them.  Ready to fight, I pop into Qeynos Hills.  They're gone though, and slowly the adrenaline seeps away as I gather up the confidence to loot my corpse and zip off to the flanks near the zone to pick up some bats.  I re-ding on my first bat... seems they knocked me back to level 5 on that kill.  Anyway, I kill some bats for the next hour... this time avoiding ALL even conning bad guys.<br>
<br>
After I'm loaded up, I head back to bank a few more copper.  I gate back to the newbie area.  Gate at level 6 takes up like 75% of your mana.  So, PvP newbie that I am, I take off anyway towards the Qeynos Hills zone.  Zap!  I'm rooted.  I spin around and see a Mage (I think it was a Mage at least) off in the distance behind me.  WHAM!  He hits me with a DD spell.  I try and get a mez off on him, but it fizzles and I don't have any mana after that.  I'm stuck.  WHAM!, another DD hits me.  Finally the root breaks and I zip off to the zone.  A foot from it, a last DD hits me and I die.<br>
<br>
That brings me to my PvP rule.  I generally, won't <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>start</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> a fight unless one of the following conditions are met:<br>
<br>
1. You've attacked me for no reason and killed me in the past.<br>
2. You're killing a friend of mine.<br>
3. You've been ganking people in the zone for no reason and this is a chance to teach you a lesson.<br>
4. I'm in *really* bad mood.<br>
<br>
Those three go in the #1 category and therefore, are KOS to me until I settle the tab up.  Welcome to notes.txt!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   [Sat Jun 30 17:56:06 2001] Tokar<br>
[Sat Jun 30 17:56:30 2001] Fawlty</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Unfortunately, I forgot to write down the name of that third dude who killed me... but I sure won't forget to write 'em down from now on.<br>
<br>
At this point, I meet my first even con Ally in the bank.  His name is Kwaichang and he's a really good dude.  Kwai gives me a Polar Bear skin so that I can head to Everfrost and have a cloak made.  I thank him profusely, say my goodbye, bank all my crap and head off to make the trip to Everfrost.<br>
<br>
Evidently, Everfrost is the only Good held area in Antonica.  Since earlier, I had made the run to Greater Faydark and seen the &quot;Good&quot; held territory there... I opted to get my ass to Everfrost and make it my new home and think about doing my hunting in Black Burrow later.<br>
<br>
Everfrost doesn't disappoint.  For the most part, it is held by the Good team.  I have to say, I was totally relieved to make it there and be amongst friends.  Occasionally, a Neutral PvP-level player would stroll through, but for the most part, we left them alone unless they attacked us.<br>
<br>
Well, I hook up with a group and start to hunt.  After a while, I meet up with a higher level player named Animon.  Another stand up dude.  He gave me a bind, showed me a good newbie quest and suggested that I show all newbie Goods the way as he has shown me.  Sounded very &quot;Obi-Wan like&quot;, so he went on my friends list right away.<br>
<br>
So, to cut this story short(er), I engaged in my first group Vs. group PvP encounter.  That ended in a draw as the higher level enemy kept running away to either the guards or some other anti-PvP NPC when our lower level superior number finally whittled them down.  Regardless, it was fun.<br>
<br>
I got to meet Wix (Pumpkin, Neutral Shaman) for the first time.  Nice dude also.  We got to talking and later in the day, he couldn't resist waxing me as I was running from some Mammoths that were trained on my group.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   [Sun Jul 01 16:25:17 2001] Pumpkin</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Bastage.  I'll get you one of these days!<br>
<br>
At the end of Sunday, I finally managed to hit level 8.  I'm broke as hell though, still using my newbie dagger and robe and with none of my level 8 spells.<br>
<br>
I never got my first PvP kill.  My spells before 8 are simply not offensively oriented.  But now that changes and as soon as I can afford blind, root, nuke and cancel magic spells -- I'll finally be able to hold my own.<br>
<br>
Anyway, that was my first experience on Sullon Zek.  I am having an absolute BLAST (no pun inte...) and I've got that &quot;I can't wait to get home from work and try this or that&quot; feeling again.  Such fun.<br>
