<br>
A great area to learn the ropes.<br>
<br>
My only problem thus far has been money.  Black Burrow would be my natural turn to, but it's held by Neutrals.  Although, they'd prolly leave me alone for a while, it's just a matter of time before a group decides that my presence is not needed in their area.<br>
<br>
Once that happens, everyone jumps in for the gank.  They're like ants.<br>
<br>
In the post I mention a trip over to Greater Faydark.  I decided to make the trip there because I heard that the Good team was populating and controlling that area and Crushbone.  That trip was really interesting.  I made the journey with not much of a problem.  I did it at level 5 to see what the control zones were.<br>
<br>
Once you hit the Karanas, it's dangerous for Goods.  There are Neutrals and Evils everywhere out in the hinter lands, they like to gank, and gank a lot.<br>
<br>
Highpass was pretty much empty.<br>
<br>
Let me tell you, Kithcor at night when you're a level 5 Human is NOT a fun experience.  Even after knowing the zone from the numerous epic General practice raids, I was pretty jacked when I got through untouched.<br>
<br>
The Commons are totally Evil.  You could see them just ITCHING to kick my ass while I ran past them.  I can only liken it to putting a hungry polar bear in a cage that's in the middle of the baby seal tank at the zoo.<br>
<br>
I won't be visiting that area any time soon without either some serious backup or a friggin' SEAL platoon.<br>
<br>
Butcherblock is totally Neutral owned.  It's also really, really loud and obnoxious.  I got out of there as fast as I could.  The Skeleton chessboard is defiantly out of the question for a good while.  I suspect that if the Goods and Neutrals don't form some sort of understood alliance against the Evils, this zone will become one hellova hot spot.  It's a gank team's heaven.<br>
<br>
Greater Faydark is... a nightmare.  Imagine Faymart x4.  Now if you're from a blue server, add PvP to the mix and it's more akin to East Harlem (you're Bruce Willis).  It's FILLED with this hodgepodge of Neutrals and Goods.  It's also very easy to not have good SA (situational awareness) in here.  I was invis'd near the Crushbone entrance just listening to the chatter and talking with Pumpkin... deciding if I should get bound or port back to Qeynos and I saw several people get pick pocketed, ganked and generally fooked with.<br>
<br>
Crushbone or no Crushbone, I ported out of there after about a half hour.<br>
<br>
Yippe ki yaay mofakka.<br>
<br>
PS.  The person who made the decision to make Tiny Daggers only available in Erudin should be rolled up in a rug and dumped in the East River next to Hoffa.  Ass.<br>
